{"type":"text","timestamp":1775870798862,"sessionID":"ses_285daca2dffetuopp54L7bgIWw","part":{"id":"prt_d7a257a9e001f9LKedFbxUrny2","messageID":"msg_d7a25587b001GK1bTqUk0Di2Ak","sessionID":"ses_285daca2dffetuopp54L7bgIWw","type":"text","text":"I'll write a delta-spec.md for AR-024 — DockerService 封装.","time":{"start":1775870798859,"end":1775870798859}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870798890,"sessionID":"ses_285daca2dffetuopp54L7bgIWw","part":{"id":"prt_d7a25ec0f001MolhPLCqBBhfEE","messageID":"msg_d7a25587b001GK1bTqUk0Di2Ak","sessionID":"ses_285daca2dffetuopp54L7bgIWw","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-39cc8202f9d64b6d95a66721356144ce","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR**: AR-024  \n**Module**: cmd/cli  \n**Language**: Python  \n**Size**: M  \n**Purpose**: Enhance and formalize the `DockerService` class to provide a robust, well-encapsulated interface for Docker operations including image building, pushing, tagging, and management.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: DockerService initialization and availability checking\nThe system SHALL provide a `DockerService` class that initializes with optional verbose logging and checks Docker availability upon construction or via explicit method calls.\n\n#### Scenario: Initialize with verbose logging\n- **GIVEN** a developer creates a `DockerService` instance with `verbose=True`\n- **WHEN** the service initializes\n- **THEN** the service SHALL store the verbose flag and use it for logging all Docker operations\n\n#### Scenario: Check Docker availability\n- **GIVEN** a `DockerService` instance\n- **WHEN** `check_docker_available()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL attempt to connect to the Docker daemon and return `True` if successful, `False` otherwise\n- **AND** if verbose is enabled, SHALL log the availability check result\n\n#### Scenario: Docker unavailable error\n- **GIVEN** Docker daemon is not running or not installed\n- **WHEN** `check_docker_available()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `False` and if verbose is enabled, log a warning message explaining the failure\n\n### Requirement: Docker image building\nThe system SHALL provide a method to build Docker images from a Dockerfile with configurable build arguments, tags, and context paths.\n\n#### Scenario: Build image with default tag\n- **GIVEN** a valid Dockerfile path and context directory\n- **WHEN** `build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path, image_name)` is called without specifying a tag\n- **THEN** the system SHALL build the image with tag `\"latest\"` and return a dict containing `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, and `build_time`\n\n#### Scenario: Build image with custom tag\n- **GIVEN** a valid Dockerfile path and context directory\n- **WHEN** `build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path, image_name, tag=\"v1.0.0\")` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL build the image with the specified tag and return image information\n\n#### Scenario: Build image with build arguments\n- **GIVEN** a Dockerfile that expects build arguments\n- **WHEN** `build_image(..., build_args={\"HTTP_PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\"})` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL pass the build arguments to Docker during the build process\n\n#### Scenario: Build failure handling\n- **GIVEN** an invalid Dockerfile or build context\n- **WHEN** `build_image()` encounters a build error\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an appropriate exception with descriptive error message\n- **AND** if verbose is enabled, SHALL log the build logs before raising the exception\n\n### Requirement: Docker image information retrieval\nThe system SHALL provide methods to retrieve detailed information about Docker images including size, creation time, and metadata.\n\n#### Scenario: Get image info for existing image\n- **GIVEN** a Docker image exists locally with name and tag\n- **WHEN** `get_image_info(\"myimage:latest\")` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a dict containing `image_id`, `image_size` (human-readable), `created`, and `tags`\n\n#### Scenario: Format size in human-readable format\n- **GIVEN** an image size in bytes (e.g., 2147483648)\n- **WHEN** the system formats the size\n- **THEN** the result SHALL be in human-readable format (e.g., \"2.0 GB\" or \"2 GiB\")\n\n#### Scenario: Get info for non-existent image\n- **GIVEN** an image name that does not exist locally\n- **WHEN** `get_image_info()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an appropriate exception (e.g., `ImageNotFoundError`) with descriptive message\n\n### Requirement: Docker image pushing to registry\nThe system SHALL provide a method to push Docker images to container registries with optional authentication and tagging.\n\n#### Scenario: Push image without authentication\n- **GIVEN** a local image exists and a public registry URL\n- **WHEN** `push_image(image_name=\"myimage\", registry_url=\"registry.example.com\")` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL tag the image for the registry and push it\n- **AND** return a dict containing `pushed_image` and `push_time`\n\n#### Scenario: Push image with authentication\n- **GIVEN** a local image and a private registry requiring credentials\n- **WHEN** `push_image(image_name=\"myimage\", registry_url=\"registry.example.com\", username=\"user\", password=\"pass\")` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL first authenticate with the registry using Docker login\n- **AND** then tag and push the image\n- **AND** return push result information\n\n#### Scenario: Push image requires re-tagging\n- **GIVEN** a local image with name \"myimage:latest\" and registry URL \"registry.example.com/username\"\n- **WHEN** `push_image()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL re-tag the image to \"registry.example.com/username/myimage:latest\" before pushing\n\n#### Scenario: Push failure handling\n- **GIVEN** network connectivity issues or authentication failures\n- **WHEN** `push_image()` encounters an error\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an appropriate exception with descriptive error message\n- **AND** if verbose is enabled, SHALL log the push attempt details\n\n### Requirement: Docker image removal\nThe system SHALL provide a method to remove Docker images from the local Docker daemon.\n\n#### Scenario: Remove existing image\n- **GIVEN** a Docker image exists locally\n- **WHEN** `remove_image(image_name)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL remove the image and return `True`\n- **AND** if verbose is enabled, SHALL log the removal operation\n\n#### Scenario: Remove non-existent image\n- **GIVEN** an image name that does not exist locally\n- **WHEN** `remove_image(image_name)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `False` and if verbose is enabled, log a warning message\n\n#### Scenario: Remove image with force option\n- **GIVEN** an image that is in use or has dependent containers\n- **WHEN** `remove_image(image_name, force=True)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL attempt to force-remove the image\n- **AND** return `True` if successful, `False` otherwise\n\n### Requirement: Docker registry authentication\nThe system SHALL provide methods to authenticate with Docker registries using username/password credentials.\n\n#### Scenario: Login to registry with SDK\n- **GIVEN** registry credentials (username and password)\n- **WHEN** `_docker_login_sdk(registry_url, username, password)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use Docker SDK to authenticate with the registry\n- **AND** raise an exception if authentication fails\n\n#### Scenario: Login to default Docker Hub\n- **GIVEN** Docker Hub credentials without specifying a registry URL\n- **WHEN** `_docker_login_sdk(None, username, password)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL authenticate with Docker Hub (default registry)\n\n### Requirement: Docker image tagging\nThe system SHALL provide methods to tag Docker images with new names or repository paths.\n\n#### Scenario: Tag image for registry\n- **GIVEN** a local image \"myimage:latest\"\n- **WHEN** `_tag_image_sdk(\"myimage:latest\", \"registry.example.com/username/myimage:v1.0\")` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a new tag for the image pointing to the specified registry path\n\n#### Scenario: Tag non-existent source image\n- **GIVEN** a source image that does not exist\n- **WHEN** `_tag_image_sdk()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an exception with descriptive message\n\n### Requirement: Verbose logging and error reporting\nThe system SHALL provide consistent verbose logging across all Docker operations and meaningful error messages for failures.\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose logging during build\n- **GIVEN** `verbose=True` when creating `DockerService`\n- **WHEN** `build_image()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL log build progress including each step of the Docker build process\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose logging during push\n- **GIVEN** `verbose=True` and an image push operation\n- **WHEN** `push_image()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL log push progress including layers being transferred\n\n#### Scenario: Descriptive error messages\n- **GIVEN** any Docker operation fails\n- **WHEN** an exception is raised\n- **THEN** the exception message SHALL include context about the operation, image name, and root cause of the failure\n\n---\n\n## Non-Functional Requirements\n\n### Performance\n- `check_docker_available()` SHALL complete within 5 seconds\n- `build_image()` SHALL stream build logs in real-time and not buffer entire output before returning on error\n- `push_image()` SHALL stream push progress and handle large images efficiently\n\n### Reliability\n- The service SHALL handle temporary network failures during push operations with appropriate error messages\n- The service SHALL validate input parameters before initiating Docker operations\n- The service SHALL use Docker SDK's built-in retry mechanisms where applicable\n\n### Maintainability\n- The service SHALL encapsulate Docker SDK complexity behind a clean, high-level API\n- Private methods SHALL start with underscore to indicate internal use\n- The service SHALL not leak Docker SDK exceptions directly to callers without appropriate wrapping\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `DockerService` can be initialized with optional verbose logging\n- [ ] `check_docker_available()` returns correct availability status\n- [ ] `build_image()` successfully builds images with default and custom tags\n- [ ] `build_image()` accepts and applies build arguments\n- [ ] `get_image_info()` returns correct image metadata\n- [ ] `push_image()` successfully pushes to public and private registries\n- [ ] `push_image()` handles authentication properly\n- [ ] `remove_image()` removes existing images and returns appropriate status\n- [ ] Verbose logging works across all operations\n- [ ] All error paths provide meaningful error messages\n- [ ] Image tagging works correctly for registry preparation\n- [ ] Service handles non-existent images gracefully\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n- The `DockerService` SHALL use `docker.from_env()` to initialize the Docker client\n- All file paths SHALL be validated to exist before Docker operations\n- Image names and tags SHALL follow Docker naming conventions\n- The service SHALL be thread-safe for concurrent read operations\n- Timeout configurations should be considered for long-running build and push operations","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775870798881,"end":1775870798888}}}}
